snippet.textDisplay:
'windows keys is an enemy"

I mean....no, they're incredibly useful, yes, they can be annoying in games, but the keyboard I currently have literally solved that issue


It's a Turtle Beach Impact 100 (Membrane, but it's been called one of the best Membrane keyboards, well, ever) and it's lil trick, you press down both Windows keys, for either 3 or 5 seconds, can't remember, until a light turns on is my routine, and that activated "WimLk" basically, turning off functionality of the Windows keys, so if you accidentally bump them whilst gaming, you don't get shoved out, and that way if a game freezes up or something, turn 'em back on, and use them to get out, so everybody wins

If you really just wanted to go ballin' to the point of pointlessness though, ZealPC Tealios are about as ballin' as linear switches get.
